Update vg-controller.js

The autoplay watcher $scope.$watch("vgAutoPlay", this.onUpdateAutoPlay.bind(this)); immediately runs onUpdateAutoPlay which runs play, while the mediaElement is not yet initialized by the vgMedia directive. Resulting in an error stating: "mediaElement[0] undefined".  

This commit adds a mediaElement[0] stub which is overwritten when the real mediaElement is initialized. (This also solves the clearMedia undefined error).

Merge pull request #323 from alexthewilde/master

Defensive check for mediaElement in clearMedia method

Defensive check for mediaElement in clearMedia method

Prevents errors from being thrown upon calling clearMedia() when mediaElement doesn't exist. This can be the case when some form of deferred loading of vg-media has been implemented where mediaElement might not always be initialised.

Added new vg-crossorigin directive to let dev set a cross origin policy for any media file or track. close #123

Optional directive for `vg-media` to add or remove a crossorigin policy to the video object. Possible values are: "anonymous" and "use-credentials". This feature should be enabled if you want to have your subtitles or video files on a different domain than the video player. Additionally you need to add CORS policies to your video and track files to your server to make it work.

I recommend this Chrome extension for testing purposes https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/allow-control-allow-origi/nlfbmbojpeacfghkpbjhddihlkkiljbi/reviews

Merge pull request #181 from UzEE/master

Fixed a bug which was causing an out of bounds exception

Fixed a bug which was causing an exception

When removing the node from the array, the iteration wasn't being terminated, which was causing an out of bounds error.

Since the length of links was being cached in `l`, when a node is removed from the links array, the links.length is reduced, while the cached `l` variable still has the originally cached value causing an out of bounds exception on the last iteration.

Merge pull request #154 from Frank3K/time-milliseconds

Represent time (currentTime, timeLeft, totalTime) in milliseconds instead of Date objects.

* BREAKING CHANGE *

Represent time (currentTime, timeLeft, totalTime) in milliseconds instead of Date objects. This simplifies working with timings from the API, for example in custom filters. Furthermore, this change fixes the (previously incorrect) values in the aria-value* attributes.

Other minor changes:
- Fix indent in controls.js.
- Simplify watches on scope variables related to times from the API.
- On video complete, scrubbar remains at 100%. This is in line with the currentTime, which also remains at 100% on video complete.

Merge pull request #108 from soton-ecs-2014-gdp-12/accessibility

Make Videogular controls more accessible

Make volume bar keyboard-friendly

Focussing the mute button and pressing UP or DOWN adjusts the volume by
5%.

Make vg-scrubbar keyboard- and ARIA-friendly

The scrub bar can now be focussed with the tab key, and its value can be
changed with the arrow keys. It also specifies ARIA attributes
identifying it as a slider.

Make control buttons <button>s instead of <div>s

<button>s have better keyboard accessibility, as they can be focussed
with the tab key and pressed with the space bar.
